{
  "type": "feat",
  "name": "Intoxicating Petal Style (Combat, Style)",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p><em>The roots of the Intoxicating Petal respond to your touch, shredding flesh or coming away painlessly, at your command.</em></p><p><strong>Prerequisites</strong>: Knowledge (nature) 3 ranks, one @UUID[Compendium.pf1-pow.disciplines.Item.iwfbEXyacCnVLEoH]{Intoxicating Petal} stance known</p><p><strong>Benefit</strong>: Whenever you remove sprouts from a creature, it deals an additional amount of damage equal to 2 per stack of sprout, plus an additional 1 damage per stack for each feat you have that lists Intoxicating Petal Style as a prerequisite (maximum +4 per stack). Alternatively, you may choose to deal no damage when removing sprout from a creature.</p><p>Additionally, whenever a creature becomes inflicted by 6 or more total sprout stacks by you, those sprouts flourish into a bouquet of floral colors causing them to be unable to take 5-foot steps. This effect is removed if the total sprout stacks you have inflicted on them is reduced below 6. </p>",
      "instructions": ""
    },
